# ─── CeyX Butler — Environment Variables ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# Never commit .env to git — it is already in .gitignore.
#
# ─── SERVER-SIDE ONLY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY lives exclusively in Vercel's environment variables
# (or your .env for local development via `vercel dev`).
# It is never prefixed with VITE_ and is never included in the browser bundle.
#
# Get your key at: https://console.anthropic.com
#
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here
#
# ─── PREVIOUSLY INSECURE (now removed) ───────────────────────────────────────
#
# VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY was the old variable. The VITE_ prefix caused Vite
# to embed it inside the compiled JavaScript that every browser downloads.
# Anyone who opened DevTools → Sources could read it and use your quota.
# This variable no longer exists anywhere in the codebase.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
